bio.experienceSummary: Hello! My name is Caroline and I have 8 years of experience working with kids. I am currently seeking my next part-time job! I recently graduated from Connecticut College where I earned a B. A. in English, and also completed extensive coursework in child development and education. Recently, I worked as a Teaching Artist for Treasure Trunk Theatre in Brooklyn, where I was responsible for a classroom on 12-16 3-5-year-olds. My other experiences include many summers of full-time nannying, coaching kids gymnastics, running a kids camp, and tutoring. I am creative, bubbly, and a favorite babysitter of many. Thank you for your consideration and I look forward to hearing from you!

Hi! My name is Nadja. I am a recent Yale graduate and currently work as a teacher in New York City. I love working and caring for kids of all ages. I have babysitting experience and also have previously worked at Basic Trust Daycare where I supported children ages (0-7). I love fostering children's curiosity through art, music, and reading with kids.

description.originalText:
Nadja is the best. She played, sang, and entertained my baby all the time. She is very energetic, passionate and caring person. My son had instant connection with her. 
Definitely would hire her again.

bio.experienceSummary: Hello, my name is Unica. I am a college student, aspiring to be a pediatric or NICU nurse one day. I reliable, patient, understanding and caring. I've been back up nanny taking cares of babies since 2019. I've worked with children between the ages of 5 months- 12 years old. I have also helped with meal preparation, light housekeeping, homework and laundry when needed. I love helping kids build their literacy through reading books, imagination playing and creative art.

description.originalText: Unica was amazing and accommodated my last minute need for a sitter. She went above and beyond with her communication and even sent pictures. My children were comfortable and really enjoyed her! Responsible, Caring and made booking a sitter an easy experience!

bio.experienceSummary:
While I work full-time in a corporate job, I love working with children and miss my days babysitting and nannying. As a way to supplement my income, I am looking to provide occasional date-night or weeknight support. I am a trustworthy, responsible caregiver that can adjust to whatever the typical routine of the family is. My ideal situation would to be find families to babysit for semi-regularly, so that we can work with each others' schedules and the kids can feel comfortable with me as a regular sitter. 

I have experience with children of all ages, from a few months to pre-teens and am always down to play games, help with schoolwork, or be active when babysitting.

Hello! My name is Agnes, and I'm currently a student with 10+ years experience as a babysitter, nanny, and house sitter. have volunteered for big brother/big sister-type programs for spending time with elementary-age children since high school. I am creative, energetic, and have experience taking care of children ages 2 and up. Please feel free to contact, so I may answer any questions you have. Thank you!

Hello families, I'm Lotoya. I'm a reliable, fun, honest, trustworthy, energetic, patient, and a responsible person. I'm interesting in a part time afternoon position working as sitter/nanny to fulfill the needs of your child/children and your family. Which I'm qualified for, with my experiences working as a sitter for 12 years and presently a certified Teacher's Assistants also CPR trained. (Having Experience working with children on the Spectrum). Currently in college to pursue my career as a teacher. My responsibilities includes picking up from school/school bus or daycare, bath, story time, preparing snacks and dinner, help with homework, Art and craft, after school activities, light cleaning, play date, outdoor activities when weather permits and bed time routine. Thanks for your interest in my profile. Great references!. Looking forward to work with you and your family . Thank you!

description.originalText: Lotoya watched our 2year old for a couple weeks full time and was absolutely wonderful. Our daughter can be a little shy but she warmed up quickly to Lotoya and was happy to see her each morning. Lotoya was on-time, easy to communicate with and very sweet. Highly recommend!

bio.experienceSummary:
As a caring and experienced childcare provider with three years in the field, I'm enthusiastic about nurturing and supporting children's growth and development. My passion for childcare stems from my previous babysitting roles, where I discovered the joy of positively impacting children's lives. I firmly believe in providing a safe, nurturing, and stimulating environment for children to thrive.

My patient, calm, and friendly nature allows me to connect with children effortlessly. I believe in open communication with parents and regularly provide updates about their child's day, using their preferred method of communication.

When it comes to enforcing household rules, I follow the parents' lead, ensuring consistency and respect for their parenting style. My approach to play includes a mix of outdoor sports, board games, puzzles, and educational games that encourage learning.

With my CPR and First Aid training, you can trust that your child is in safe hands.

description.originalText: Wonderful babysitter, my child loves her.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi! My name is Ruah! I just moved to Brooklyn from Seattle, after graduation from undergrad last spring. I am an actor who loves kids, being outside and free play. I am looking for families who need recurrent or long-term childcare in the area.

I have over 9 years of experience taking care of children ranging in age from 4 months to 13 years old. I am CPR certified (2024) and comfortable in feeding, changing, putting to sleep, and playing with children of all ages. I have also worked with kids in classroom and camp settings. In college, I completed Cleveland Playhouse's CARE program where I learned and practiced trauma-informed teaching in local K-8's.

As an actor, I easily entertain and engage with children, I'm passionate and playful, while also solid and effective in my communication. 

Feel free to reach out via the app with any questions!

description.originalText: Ruah is great with my child! She is fun, caring, and my daughter adores her.

bio.experienceSummary:
Hi Everyone! My name is Mira, I recently moved to New York city from DC to explore the city and take some time off before I go to law school in the fall.

I am active and energetic, and I love children. I enjoy skiing, running, swimming, cooking, and arts and crafts! I will bring this sort of energy into my time with your children, but I also understand that safety is the top priority. 

I am experienced with caring for multiple children at a time at a variety of different ages. I also have many years of experience tutoring elementary and middle school children, so I am able to help with schooling and homework. I am certified in babysitting, First Aid, and CPR, and I speak some Spanish. 

I would love to hear from you and can provide references upon request! 

Thanks, 
Mira

I am the oldest of 5 children with my youngest sibling being 10 years old. I have been babysitting and nannying for 10+ years and have enjoyed every opportunity I get to care for kids. I have experience with a wide range of age groups from infants to 12+ year olds. Families I have previously cared for say that I am kind, attentive, fun, compassionate, responsible, and always with a smile on my face. I make sure the children are happy and well cared for while under my supervision. I will play with them and make sure the home is tidy when you return.

description.displayText: Sophia is wonderful with the kids and always on time and dependable! She plays with the kids, is creative and fun and always cleans up when they are done. You would be lucky to have her watch your kids!
description.originalText: Sophia is wonderful with the kids and always on time and dependable! She plays with the kids, is creative and fun and always cleans up when they are done. You would be lucky to have her watch your kids!
